        r"In the context $x_1 \ldots x_{n-1}$, $q$ appears $t$ times at indices $q_1, \ldots, q_t$ ($1 \le q_1 \le q_t \le n-1$).\n\n"
        r"Continuation token $x_{n+1}$ is defined by: $t = 1$ and $x_{n+1} = x_{q_1-1}$\n\n"
        r"Examples:\n"
        r"7ovjWj:v

qMhvoM:q
